### 2ï¸âƒ£ Unsupervised Learning (Finding Patterns in Unlabeled Data) 
ğŸ“Œ How It Works: 
- The model only receives input data, with no predefined labels.  
- It identifies patterns and clusters on its own.  
ğŸ“Œ Examples:  
âœ… Customer segmentation â€“ Grouping customers based on buying behavior.  
âœ… Anomaly detection â€“ Identifying fraudulent transactions.  
ğŸ›  Common Algorithms:  
- K-Means Clustering  
